title: The Earth's Last Defender Theme
info:
By: Killer Fish (Todd Showalter)
   of Late Nite Software Labs   
--------------------------------
Written on or about Mar/94.  (c)
  This song is dedicated to my  
abiding obsession with Japanese 
Anime.  Don't ask me what the   
two have to do with each other. 
  Anyways, enjoy the music, and 
I would like to appologize in   
advance for any disco-like stuff
in the song.  It's not my fault,
really.  Blame someone else.    
  I said that I would eventually
deliver an ULT file that was    
wider than 10 channels, and here
it is.  Don't bug me about the  
quality, that wasn't part of the
deal.  I'll work on making the  
the next one sound better.      
  If you're looking for a really
good sample for making chords,  
get a copy of the sample called 
"Polysynth Lead I", above.  Its 
really quite good to work with, 
and it is devoid of irritating  
harmonics, so chords don't sound
odd with it.                    
  Well, I'm just about out of   
scrawling space, so I'll sign   
off now.  Gotta speed, keid...
